x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">When mega-famous at=
hletes look to leverage their influence and credibility past their playing =
days, many inevitably follow a tried and true path: They find a business pa=
rtner and form a production company. <b>Peyton Manning</b>, who launched Om=
aha Productions with <b>Jamie Horowitz</b> in 2020, recently received an in=
vestment from The Chernin Group valuing the company at more than $400 milli=
on following the success of shows like <i>Quarterback</i>. (Yes, that=E2=80=
=99s an insane valuation in this environment, but so it goes=E2=80=A6) <br/=
><br/>Some precocious stars even set up their shingles <i>during</i> their =
careers. <b>Gerry Cardinale</b>=E2=80=99s RedBird Capital took a minority p=
osition in <b>LeBron James</b>=E2=80=99s SpringHill, in 2021, that valued t=
he company at $725 million. (<i>Hmm</i>, maybe that Omaha number isn=E2=80=
=99t so crazy after all=E2=80=A6) Last week, I <u><a href=3D"https://email.=
puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dTTVZCbkRmZ3BkUDFNb=
